LuaScript:
--[[ Lua code. See documentation: http://berserk-games.com/knowledgebase/scripting/ --]]

--[[ The OnLoad function. This is called after everything in the game save finishes loading.
Most of your script code goes here. --]]

omen_deck_id = "aa006b"
api_status = false
api_address = "http://127.0.0.1:5000/"

function onload()
    ping_api()
    omen_deck = getObjectFromGUID(omen_deck_id)

    omen_button = {}
    omen_button.click_function = 'deal_omen_card'
    omen_button.function_owner = nil
    omen_button.label = 'Deal Omen Card'
    omen_button.position = {2,0,0}
    omen_button.rotation = {0,0,0}
    omen_button.width = 800
    omen_button.height = 500
    omen_button.font_size = 100
    omen_button.tooltip = "I'm A Button!"
    omen_deck.createButton(omen_button)


    omen_deck_contents = omen_deck.getObjects()
    

    --[[ print('Onload!') --]]
end

function ping_api()
    WebRequest.get(api_address, function(result)
        print(result.is_error)
        if result.is_error 
        then 
            print(result.error)
            api_status = false
        else 
            api_status = true
        end
    end)
end


function deal_omen_card(obj, color, alt_click)
    print(color)
    if api_status then
        WebRequest.put(api_address.."dealOmen", JSON.encode(obj.getObjects()), function(result)
            print(result.text)
            parameters = {}
            parameters.guid = result.text
            parameters.callback_function = function(obj) 
                dealt_card = getObjectFromGUID(obj.getGUID())
                dealt_card.deal(1, color)
            end
            obj.takeObject(parameters)
        end)
    else
        obj.shuffle()
        obj.deal(1, color)
    end
    
end

--[[ The Update function. This is called once per frame. --]]
function update ()
        --[[ print('Update loop!') --]]
end

11.Name: Custom_Tile
11.Description:
Pages 19-20

SEE NOTEBOOK RULES FOR HAUNT 68

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile
ContainedObjects.Description:
Once during an explorer's turn, if that explorer is in either room, he or she can attempt a Knowledge roll to use the Wall Switch:
3+: That explorer finds the hidden switch and goes through. This doesn't count as moving a space.
0-2: That explorer can't find the hidden switch and can't go through.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile
ContainedObjects.Description: The Smoke blocks line of sight from adjacent rooms. An explorer rolls 2 fewer dice (minimum of 1 die) on all trait rolls while in this room.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile
ContainedObjects.Description:
Once during an explorer's turn, that explorer can attempt a Might roll to use the Slide:
5+: You control the Slide. Put yourself in any explored room on any floor below the Slide.
0-4: Draw tiles from the room stack until you draw a basement room. (If no basement rooms are in the stack choose a basement room in play.) You fall to that room and take 1 die of physical damage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile
ContainedObjects.Description:
Once during an explorer's turn, that explorer can attempt a Sanity roll to search the Skeletons:
5+ Draw an item card. Remove the Skeletons token.
0-4: You dig around, but find nothing. Take 1 die of mental damage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile_Stack
ContainedObjects.Description:
Any explorer can use the Secret Stairs. An explorer can't end his or her turn in the stairs.

Moving from one Secret Stairs token to the other counts as moving one space. (The stairs don't count as a space.)

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile_Stack
ContainedObjects.Description:
Any explorer can use the Secret Passage. An explorer can't end his or her turn in the passage.

Moving from one Secret Passage token to the other counts as moving one space. (The passage itself doesn't count as a space.)

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile
ContainedObjects.Description:
Once during an explorer's turn, that explorer can attempt a Knowledge roll to open the Safe:
5+: Draw 2 item cards and remove the Safe token.
2-4: Take 1 die of physical damage. The Safe won't open.
0-1: Take 2 dice of physical damagee. The Safe won't open.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile
ContainedObjects.Description: Each explorer rolls 1 fewer die (minimum 1) on all trait rolls while in this room.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile
ContainedObjects.Description:
Once during an explorer's turn, that explorer can roll 2 dice to open the Closet:
4: Draw an item card.
2-3: Draw an event card.
0-1: Draw an event card and remove the Closet token.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile
ContainedObjects.Description: When an explorer exits this room after the haunt is revealed, the corpse attacks. The player on the explorer's right makes a Might 4 attack against the explorer. If the explorer wins by 3 or more, discard the token.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Tile
ContainedObjects.Description: Each hero rolls 1 addtional die (maximum of 8 dice) on all trait rolls while in this room.

11.title: Mod Info
11.body:
The haunt chart is in the new rule book next to the white character.  The older one is the first page in the older Traitor's tome.

Characters are finally reversable unlike older mods of this game.  Simply flip the characters over to see the alternative.

The two hidden areas are for the haunt.  Set both of them to the same color as the traitor's seat.  One of them is marked visable only to that color, the other is invisble only to that color.

Player hands are set up to be visable to everyone. Carried Items/Omens are public knowledge.

There is currently no way to not use the expansion without manually removing all of the expansion's cards, tiles, and tokens from the table.  A full count of objects is in the rule books.

17.title: Rules FAQ
17.body:
In the trait-adding rooms, how do the explorer tokens work?

Put your explorer token on the room when you activate its power at the end of your turn. In the base set, these tiles should be adjusted to account for your explorer token.

Solution: On the base set’s room tiles Chapel, Gymnasium, Larder, and Library, after “if you end your turn here,” add “put your explorer token here and”.



In Acupuncture, do I go to an adjacent room whether I lose 1 Sanity or attempt the Might roll?

No, only if you lose the Sanity.

Solution:
On the event card Acupuncture, change “Go to an adjacent, discovered room and lose 1 Sanity, or attempt a Might roll:” to “You may go to an adjacent, discovered room and lose 1 Sanity. If you don’t, attempt a Might roll:”



Do I have to walk through the Misty Arch?

No.

Solution:
On the event card Misty Arch, change “Remove your figure” to “If you do, remove your figure”.



In Haunt 68, He Who Must Not Be Read, can Maldovo attack only with Might?

No, he can also attack with Sanity.

Solution:
In the Traitor’s Tome for Haunt 68, add a paragraph after the first bullet of Special Attack Rules that reads, “You may attack with Might or Sanity. Your Might attack deals physical damage and your Sanity attack deals mental damage.”



In Haunt 68, He Who Must Not Be Read, what trait values does a Wraith have?

The explorer’s starting values.

Solution:
In the Traitor’s Tome for Haunt 68, in Special Attack Rules after “becomes a Wraith”, add “with traits equal to the explorer’s starting values.”
